Sequence Information.Family: Belongs to the gastrin/cholecystokinin family (Magainin subfamily)
Sequence Information.Target Organism: No MICs found in DRAMP database
Sequence Information.Hemolytic Activity: No hemolysis information or data found in the reference(s) presented in this entry
Sequence Information.Structure Description: The peptide assumed α-helices in the lipid environment, as characterized by double minima around 208 and 222 nm. The [θ]222 value, a measure of helicity, of I (−17,900 deg cm2 dmol−1) was ca. 20% smaller than that of F16W-MG2 (−23,200 deg cm2 dmol−1).
Sequence Information.Function: The peptide-induced membrane permeabilization was examined on the basis of the efflux of the fluorescent dye calcein from egg PG LUVs. The mutant I (F5Y, F16W-MG2) showed a slightly weaker but comparable leakage activity compared with F16W-MG2.

Literature.Title: Effects of peptide dimerization on pore formation Antiparallel disulfide-dimerized magainin 2 analogue.
Literature.Author: Hara T, Kodama H, Kondo M, Wakamatsu K, Takeda A, Tachi T, Matsuzaki K.
